37/* This method assumes that |stream_size_bytes| is in valid range,
38 * i.e. >= 0 && <= STREAM_MAXW16_60MS
39 */
40static void InitializeDecoderBitstream(size_t stream_size_bytes,
41 Bitstr_dec* bitstream) {
42 bitstream->W_upper = 0xFFFFFFFF;
43 bitstream->streamval = 0;
44 bitstream->stream_index = 0;
45 bitstream->full = 1;
46 bitstream->stream_size = (stream_size_bytes + 1) >> 1;
47 memset(bitstream->stream, 0, sizeof(bitstream->stream));
48}

50/****************************************************************************
51 * WebRtcIsacfix_Create(...)
52 *
53 * This function creates a ISAC instance, which will contain the state
54 * information for one coding/decoding channel.
55 *
56 * Input:
57 * - *ISAC_main_inst : a pointer to the coder instance.
58 *
59 * Return value : 0 - Ok
60 * -1 - Error
61 */
62
63int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_Create(ISACFIX_MainStruct **ISAC_main_inst)
64{
65 ISACFIX_SubStruct *tempo;
66 tempo = malloc(1 * sizeof(ISACFIX_SubStruct));
67 *ISAC_main_inst = (ISACFIX_MainStruct *)tempo;
68 if (*ISAC_main_inst!=NULL) {
69 (*(ISACFIX_SubStruct**)ISAC_main_inst)->errorcode = 0;
70 (*(ISACFIX_SubStruct**)ISAC_main_inst)->initflag = 0;
71 (*(ISACFIX_SubStruct**)ISAC_main_inst)->ISACenc_obj.SaveEnc_ptr = NULL;
72 WebRtcIsacfix_InitBandwidthEstimator(&tempo->bwestimator_obj);
73 return(0);
74 } else {
75 return(-1);
76 }
77}

80/****************************************************************************
81 * WebRtcIsacfix_CreateInternal(...)
82 *
83 * This function creates the memory that is used to store data in the encoder
84 *
85 * Input:
86 * - *ISAC_main_inst : a pointer to the coder instance.
87 *
88 * Return value : 0 - Ok
89 * -1 - Error
90 */
91
92int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_CreateInternal(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst)
93{
94 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
95
96 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
97 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
98
99 /* Allocate memory for storing encoder data */
100 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.SaveEnc_ptr = malloc(1 * sizeof(IsacSaveEncoderData));
101
102 if (ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.SaveEnc_ptr!=NULL) {
103 return(0);
104 } else {
105 return(-1);
106 }
107}

220/****************************************************************************
221 * WebRtcIsacfix_EncoderInit(...)
222 *
223 * This function initializes a ISAC instance prior to the encoder calls.
224 *
225 * Input:
226 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
227 * - CodingMode : 0 -> Bit rate and frame length are automatically
228 * adjusted to available bandwidth on
229 * transmission channel.
230 * 1 -> User sets a frame length and a target bit
231 * rate which is taken as the maximum short-term
232 * average bit rate.
233 *
234 * Return value : 0 - Ok
235 * -1 - Error
236 */
237
238int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_EncoderInit(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
239 int16_t CodingMode)
240{
241 int k;
242 int16_t statusInit;
243 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
244
245 statusInit = 0;
246 /* typecast pointer to rela structure */
247 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
248
249 /* flag encoder init */
250 ISAC_inst->initflag |= 2;
251
252 if (CodingMode == 0)
253 /* Adaptive mode */
254 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.new_framelength = INITIAL_FRAMESAMPLES;
255 else if (CodingMode == 1)
256 /* Instantaneous mode */
257 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.new_framelength = 480; /* default for I-mode */
258 else {
259 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DISALLOWED_CODING_MODE;
260 statusInit = -1;
261 }
262
263 ISAC_inst->CodingMode = CodingMode;
264
265 WebRtcIsacfix_InitMaskingEnc(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maskfiltstr_obj);
266 WebRtcIsacfix_InitPreFilterbank(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.prefiltbankstr_obj);
267 WebRtcIsacfix_InitPitchFilter(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.pitchfiltstr_obj);
268 WebRtcIsacfix_InitPitchAnalysis(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.pitchanalysisstr_obj);
269
270 WebRtcIsacfix_InitRateModel(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.rate_data_obj);
271
272
273 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.buffer_index = 0;
274 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.frame_nb = 0;
275 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.BottleNeck = 32000; /* default for I-mode */
276 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.MaxDelay = 10; /* default for I-mode */
277 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.current_framesamples = 0;
278 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.s2nr = 0;
279 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.MaxBits = 0;
280 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.bitstr_seed = 4447;
281 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes30 = STREAM_MAXW16_30MS << 1;
282 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes60 = STREAM_MAXW16_60MS << 1;
283 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes = STREAM_MAXW16_60MS << 1;
284 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes = STREAM_MAXW16_30MS << 1;
285 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.enforceFrameSize = 0;
286
287 /* Init the bistream data area to zero */
288 for (k=0; k<STREAM_MAXW16_60MS; k++){
289 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.bitstr_obj.stream[k] = 0;
290 }
291
292 InitFunctionPointers();
293
294 return statusInit;
295}
296
297/* Read the given number of bytes of big-endian 16-bit integers from |src| and
298 write them to |dest| in host endian. If |nbytes| is odd, the number of
299 output elements is rounded up, and the least significant byte of the last
300 element is set to 0. */
301static void read_be16(const uint8_t* src, size_t nbytes, uint16_t* dest) {
302 size_t i;
303 for (i = 0; i < nbytes / 2; ++i)
304 dest[i] = src[2 * i] << 8 | src[2 * i + 1];
305 if (nbytes % 2 == 1)
306 dest[nbytes / 2] = src[nbytes - 1] << 8;
307}
308
309/* Read the given number of bytes of host-endian 16-bit integers from |src| and
310 write them to |dest| in big endian. If |nbytes| is odd, the number of source
311 elements is rounded up (but only the most significant byte of the last
312 element is used), and the number of output bytes written will be
313 nbytes + 1. */
314static void write_be16(const uint16_t* src, size_t nbytes, uint8_t* dest) {
315 size_t i;
316 for (i = 0; i < nbytes / 2; ++i) {
317 dest[2 * i] = src[i] >> 8;
318 dest[2 * i + 1] = src[i];
319 }
320 if (nbytes % 2 == 1) {
321 dest[nbytes - 1] = src[nbytes / 2] >> 8;
322 dest[nbytes] = 0;
323 }
324}

326/****************************************************************************
327 * WebRtcIsacfix_Encode(...)
328 *
329 * This function encodes 10ms frame(s) and inserts it into a package.
330 * Input speech length has to be 160 samples (10ms). The encoder buffers those
331 * 10ms frames until it reaches the chosen Framesize (480 or 960 samples
332 * corresponding to 30 or 60 ms frames), and then proceeds to the encoding.
333 *
334 * Input:
335 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
336 * - speechIn : input speech vector.
337 *
338 * Output:
339 * - encoded : the encoded data vector
340 *
341 * Return value:
342 * : >0 - Length (in bytes) of coded data
343 * : 0 - The buffer didn't reach the chosen framesize
344 * so it keeps buffering speech samples.
345 * : -1 - Error
346 */
347
348int WebRtcIsacfix_Encode(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
349 const int16_t *speechIn,
350 uint8_t* encoded)
351{
352 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
353 int stream_len;
354
355 /* typecast pointer to rela structure */
356 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
357
358
359 /* check if encoder initiated */
360 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 2) != 2) {
361 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_ENCODER_NOT_INITIATED;
362 return (-1);
363 }
364
365 stream_len = WebRtcIsacfix_EncodeImpl((int16_t*)speechIn,
366 &ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj,
367 &ISAC_inst->bwestimator_obj,
368 ISAC_inst->CodingMode);
369 if (stream_len<0) {
370 ISAC_inst->errorcode = -(int16_t)stream_len;
371 return -1;
372 }
373
374 write_be16(ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.bitstr_obj.stream, (size_t)stream_len,
375 encoded);
376 return stream_len;
377
378}

381/****************************************************************************
382 * WebRtcIsacfix_GetNewBitStream(...)
383 *
384 * This function returns encoded data, with the recieved bwe-index in the
385 * stream. It should always return a complete packet, i.e. only called once
386 * even for 60 msec frames
387 *
388 * Input:
389 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
390 * - bweIndex : index of bandwidth estimate to put in new bitstream
391 *
392 * Output:
393 * - encoded : the encoded data vector
394 *
395 * Return value:
396 * : >0 - Length (in bytes) of coded data
397 * : -1 - Error
398 */
399
400int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_GetNewBitStream(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
401 int16_t bweIndex,
402 float scale,
403 uint8_t* encoded)
404{
405 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
406 int16_t stream_len;
407
408 /* typecast pointer to rela structure */
409 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
410
411
412 /* check if encoder initiated */
413 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 2) != 2) {
414 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_ENCODER_NOT_INITIATED;
415 return (-1);
416 }
417
418 stream_len = WebRtcIsacfix_EncodeStoredData(&ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj,
419 bweIndex,
420 scale);
421 if (stream_len<0) {
422 ISAC_inst->errorcode = - stream_len;
423 return -1;
424 }
425
426 write_be16(ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.bitstr_obj.stream, stream_len, encoded);
427 return stream_len;
428}

462/****************************************************************************
463 * WebRtcIsacfix_UpdateBwEstimate1(...)
464 *
465 * This function updates the estimate of the bandwidth.
466 *
467 * Input:
468 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
469 * - encoded : encoded ISAC frame(s).
470 * - packet_size : size of the packet.
471 * - rtp_seq_number : the RTP number of the packet.
472 * - arr_ts : the arrival time of the packet (from NetEq)
473 * in samples.
474 *
475 * Return value : 0 - Ok
476 * -1 - Error
477 */
478
479int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_UpdateBwEstimate1(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
480 const uint8_t* encoded,
481 size_t packet_size,
482 uint16_t rtp_seq_number,
483 uint32_t arr_ts)
484{
485 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
486 Bitstr_dec streamdata;
487 int16_t err;
488 const size_t kRequiredEncodedLenBytes = 10;
489
490 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
491 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
492
493 /* Sanity check of packet length */
494 if (packet_size == 0) {
495 /* return error code if the packet length is null or less */
496 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_EMPTY_PACKET;
497 return -1;
498 } else if (packet_size > (STREAM_MAXW16<<1)) {
499 /* return error code if length of stream is too long */
500 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
501 return -1;
502 }
503
504 /* check if decoder initiated */
505 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 1) != 1) {
506 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DECODER_NOT_INITIATED;
507 return (-1);
508 }
509
510 InitializeDecoderBitstream(packet_size, &streamdata);
511
512 read_be16(encoded, kRequiredEncodedLenBytes, streamdata.stream);
513
514 err = WebRtcIsacfix_EstimateBandwidth(&ISAC_inst->bwestimator_obj,
515 &streamdata,
516 packet_size,
517 rtp_seq_number,
518 0,
519 arr_ts);
520
521
522 if (err < 0)
523 {
524 /* return error code if something went wrong */
525 ISAC_inst->errorcode = -err;
526 return -1;
527 }
528
529
530 return 0;
531}
532
533/****************************************************************************
534 * WebRtcIsacfix_UpdateBwEstimate(...)
535 *
536 * This function updates the estimate of the bandwidth.
537 *
538 * Input:
539 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
540 * - encoded : encoded ISAC frame(s).
541 * - packet_size : size of the packet.
542 * - rtp_seq_number : the RTP number of the packet.
543 * - send_ts : Send Time Stamp from RTP header
544 * - arr_ts : the arrival time of the packet (from NetEq)
545 * in samples.
546 *
547 * Return value : 0 - Ok
548 * -1 - Error
549 */
550
551int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_UpdateBwEstimate(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
552 const uint8_t* encoded,
553 size_t packet_size,
554 uint16_t rtp_seq_number,
555 uint32_t send_ts,
556 uint32_t arr_ts)
557{
558 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
559 Bitstr_dec streamdata;
560 int16_t err;
561 const size_t kRequiredEncodedLenBytes = 10;
562
563 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
564 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
565
566 /* Sanity check of packet length */
567 if (packet_size == 0) {
568 /* return error code if the packet length is null or less */
569 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_EMPTY_PACKET;
570 return -1;
571 } else if (packet_size < kRequiredEncodedLenBytes) {
572 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_PACKET_TOO_SHORT;
573 return -1;
574 } else if (packet_size > (STREAM_MAXW16<<1)) {
575 /* return error code if length of stream is too long */
576 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
577 return -1;
578 }
579
580 /* check if decoder initiated */
581 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 1) != 1) {
582 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DECODER_NOT_INITIATED;
583 return (-1);
584 }
585
586 InitializeDecoderBitstream(packet_size, &streamdata);
587
588 read_be16(encoded, kRequiredEncodedLenBytes, streamdata.stream);
589
590 err = WebRtcIsacfix_EstimateBandwidth(&ISAC_inst->bwestimator_obj,
591 &streamdata,
592 packet_size,
593 rtp_seq_number,
594 send_ts,
595 arr_ts);
596
597 if (err < 0)
598 {
599 /* return error code if something went wrong */
600 ISAC_inst->errorcode = -err;
601 return -1;
602 }
603
604
605 return 0;
606}

608/****************************************************************************
609 * WebRtcIsacfix_Decode(...)
610 *
611 * This function decodes a ISAC frame. Output speech length
612 * will be a multiple of 480 samples: 480 or 960 samples,
613 * depending on the framesize (30 or 60 ms).
614 *
615 * Input:
616 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
617 * - encoded : encoded ISAC frame(s)
618 * - len : bytes in encoded vector
619 *
620 * Output:
621 * - decoded : The decoded vector
622 *
623 * Return value : >0 - number of samples in decoded vector
624 * -1 - Error
625 */
626
627
628int WebRtcIsacfix_Decode(ISACFIX_MainStruct* ISAC_main_inst,
629 const uint8_t* encoded,
630 size_t len,
631 int16_t* decoded,
632 int16_t* speechType)
633{
634 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
635 /* number of samples (480 or 960), output from decoder */
636 /* that were actually used in the encoder/decoder (determined on the fly) */
637 size_t number_of_samples;
638 int declen_int = 0;
639 size_t declen;
640
641 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
642 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
643
644 /* check if decoder initiated */
645 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 1) != 1) {
646 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DECODER_NOT_INITIATED;
647 return (-1);
648 }
649
650 /* Sanity check of packet length */
651 if (len == 0) {
652 /* return error code if the packet length is null or less */
653 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_EMPTY_PACKET;
654 return -1;
655 } else if (len > (STREAM_MAXW16<<1)) {
656 /* return error code if length of stream is too long */
657 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
658 return -1;
659 }
660
661 InitializeDecoderBitstream(len, &ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj.bitstr_obj);
662
663 read_be16(encoded, len, ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj.bitstr_obj.stream);
664
665 /* added for NetEq purposes (VAD/DTX related) */
666 *speechType=1;
667
668 declen_int = WebRtcIsacfix_DecodeImpl(decoded, &ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj,
669 &number_of_samples);
670 if (declen_int < 0) {
671 /* Some error inside the decoder */
672 ISAC_inst->errorcode = -(int16_t)declen_int;
673 memset(decoded, 0, sizeof(int16_t) * MAX_FRAMESAMPLES);
674 return -1;
675 }
676 declen = (size_t)declen_int;
677
678 /* error check */
679
680 if (declen & 1) {
681 if (len != declen &&
682 len != declen +
683 ((ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj.bitstr_obj.stream[declen >> 1]) & 0xFF)) {
684 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
685 memset(decoded, 0, sizeof(int16_t) * number_of_samples);
686 return -1;
687 }
688 } else {
689 if (len != declen &&
690 len != declen +
691 ((ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj.bitstr_obj.stream[declen >> 1]) >> 8)) {
692 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
693 memset(decoded, 0, sizeof(int16_t) * number_of_samples);
694 return -1;
695 }
696 }
697
698 return (int)number_of_samples;
699}

702/****************************************************************************
703 * WebRtcIsacfix_DecodePlc(...)
704 *
705 * This function conducts PLC for ISAC frame(s) in wide-band (16kHz sampling).
706 * Output speech length will be "480*noOfLostFrames" samples
707 * that is equevalent of "30*noOfLostFrames" millisecond.
708 *
709 * Input:
710 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
711 * - noOfLostFrames : Number of PLC frames (480sample = 30ms)
712 * to produce
713 *
714 * Output:
715 * - decoded : The decoded vector
716 *
717 * Return value : Number of samples in decoded PLC vector
718 */
719
720size_t WebRtcIsacfix_DecodePlc(ISACFIX_MainStruct* ISAC_main_inst,
721 int16_t* decoded,
722 size_t noOfLostFrames)
723{
724
725 size_t no_of_samples, declen, k;
726 int16_t outframe16[MAX_FRAMESAMPLES];
727
728 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
729 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
730 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
731
732 /* Limit number of frames to two = 60 msec. Otherwise we exceed data vectors */
733 if (noOfLostFrames > 2) {
734 noOfLostFrames = 2;
735 }
736 k = 0;
737 declen = 0;
738 while( noOfLostFrames > 0 )
739 {
740 WebRtcIsacfix_DecodePlcImpl(&(outframe16[k*480]), &ISAC_inst->ISACdec_obj,
741 &no_of_samples);
742 declen += no_of_samples;
743 noOfLostFrames--;
744 k++;
745 }
746
747 for (k=0;k<declen;k++) {
748 decoded[k] = outframe16[k];
749 }
750
751 return declen;
752}

755/****************************************************************************
756 * WebRtcIsacfix_Control(...)
757 *
758 * This function sets the limit on the short-term average bit rate and the
759 * frame length. Should be used only in Instantaneous mode.
760 *
761 * Input:
762 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
763 * - rate : limit on the short-term average bit rate,
764 * in bits/second (between 10000 and 32000)
765 * - framesize : number of milliseconds per frame (30 or 60)
766 *
767 * Return value : 0 - ok
768 * -1 - Error
769 */
770
771int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_Control(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
772 int16_t rate,
773 int framesize)
774{
775 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
776 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
777 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
778
779 if (ISAC_inst->CodingMode == 0)
780 {
781 /* in adaptive mode */
782 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_MODE_MISMATCH;
783 return -1;
784 }
785
786
787 if (rate >= 10000 && rate <= 32000)
788 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.BottleNeck = rate;
789 else {
790 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DISALLOWED_BOTTLENECK;
791 return -1;
792 }
793
794
795
796 if (framesize == 30 || framesize == 60)
797 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.new_framelength = (int16_t)((FS/1000) * framesize);
798 else {
799 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DISALLOWED_FRAME_LENGTH;
800 return -1;
801 }
802
803 return 0;
804}
805
806void WebRtcIsacfix_SetInitialBweBottleneck(ISACFIX_MainStruct* ISAC_main_inst,
807 int bottleneck_bits_per_second) {
808 ISACFIX_SubStruct* inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct*)ISAC_main_inst;
809 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bottleneck_bits_per_second, 10000);
810 RTC_DCHECK_LE(bottleneck_bits_per_second, 32000);
811 inst->bwestimator_obj.sendBwAvg = ((uint32_t)bottleneck_bits_per_second) << 7;
812}

814/****************************************************************************
815 * WebRtcIsacfix_ControlBwe(...)
816 *
817 * This function sets the initial values of bottleneck and frame-size if
818 * iSAC is used in channel-adaptive mode. Through this API, users can
819 * enforce a frame-size for all values of bottleneck. Then iSAC will not
820 * automatically change the frame-size.
821 *
822 *
823 * Input:
824 * - ISAC_main_inst : ISAC instance.
825 * - rateBPS : initial value of bottleneck in bits/second
826 * 10000 <= rateBPS <= 32000 is accepted
827 * For default bottleneck set rateBPS = 0
828 * - frameSizeMs : number of milliseconds per frame (30 or 60)
829 * - enforceFrameSize : 1 to enforce the given frame-size through out
830 * the adaptation process, 0 to let iSAC change
831 * the frame-size if required.
832 *
833 * Return value : 0 - ok
834 * -1 - Error
835 */
836
837int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_ControlBwe(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
838 int16_t rateBPS,
839 int frameSizeMs,
840 int16_t enforceFrameSize)
841{
842 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
843 /* Typecast pointer to real structure */
844 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
845
846 /* check if encoder initiated */
847 if ((ISAC_inst->initflag & 2) != 2) {
848 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_ENCODER_NOT_INITIATED;
849 return (-1);
850 }
851
852 /* Check that we are in channel-adaptive mode, otherwise, return -1 */
853 if (ISAC_inst->CodingMode != 0) {
854 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_MODE_MISMATCH;
855 return (-1);
856 }
857
858 /* Set struct variable if enforceFrameSize is set. ISAC will then keep the */
859 /* chosen frame size. */
860 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.enforceFrameSize = (enforceFrameSize != 0)? 1:0;
861
862 /* Set initial rate, if value between 10000 and 32000, */
863 /* if rateBPS is 0, keep the default initial bottleneck value (15000) */
864 if ((rateBPS >= 10000) && (rateBPS <= 32000)) {
865 ISAC_inst->bwestimator_obj.sendBwAvg = (((uint32_t)rateBPS) << 7);
866 } else if (rateBPS != 0) {
867 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DISALLOWED_BOTTLENECK;
868 return -1;
869 }
870
871 /* Set initial framesize. If enforceFrameSize is set the frame size will not change */
872 if ((frameSizeMs == 30) || (frameSizeMs == 60)) {
873 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.new_framelength = (int16_t)((FS/1000) * frameSizeMs);
874 } else {
875 ISAC_inst->errorcode = ISAC_DISALLOWED_FRAME_LENGTH;
876 return -1;
877 }
878
879 return 0;
880}

946/****************************************************************************
947 * WebRtcIsacfix_ReadFrameLen(...)
948 *
949 * This function returns the length of the frame represented in the packet.
950 *
951 * Input:
952 * - encoded : Encoded bitstream
953 *
954 * Output:
955 * - frameLength : Length of frame in packet (in samples)
956 *
957 */
958
959int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_ReadFrameLen(const uint8_t* encoded,
960 size_t encoded_len_bytes,
961 size_t* frameLength)
962{
963 Bitstr_dec streamdata;
964 int16_t err;
965 const size_t kRequiredEncodedLenBytes = 10;
966
967 if (encoded_len_bytes < kRequiredEncodedLenBytes) {
968 return -1;
969 }
970
971 InitializeDecoderBitstream(encoded_len_bytes, &streamdata);
972
973 read_be16(encoded, kRequiredEncodedLenBytes, streamdata.stream);
974
975 /* decode frame length */
976 err = WebRtcIsacfix_DecodeFrameLen(&streamdata, frameLength);
977 if (err<0) // error check
978 return err;
979
980 return 0;
981}

984/****************************************************************************
985 * WebRtcIsacfix_ReadBwIndex(...)
986 *
987 * This function returns the index of the Bandwidth estimate from the bitstream.
988 *
989 * Input:
990 * - encoded : Encoded bitstream
991 *
992 * Output:
993 * - frameLength : Length of frame in packet (in samples)
994 * - rateIndex : Bandwidth estimate in bitstream
995 *
996 */
997
998int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_ReadBwIndex(const uint8_t* encoded,
999 size_t encoded_len_bytes,
1000 int16_t* rateIndex)
1001{
1002 Bitstr_dec streamdata;
1003 int16_t err;
1004 const size_t kRequiredEncodedLenBytes = 10;
1005
1006 if (encoded_len_bytes < kRequiredEncodedLenBytes) {
1007 return -1;
1008 }
1009
1010 InitializeDecoderBitstream(encoded_len_bytes, &streamdata);
1011
1012 read_be16(encoded, kRequiredEncodedLenBytes, streamdata.stream);
1013
1014 /* decode frame length, needed to get to the rateIndex in the bitstream */
1015 size_t frameLength;
1016 err = WebRtcIsacfix_DecodeFrameLen(&streamdata, &frameLength);
1017 if (err<0) // error check
1018 return err;
1019
1020 /* decode BW estimation */
1021 err = WebRtcIsacfix_DecodeSendBandwidth(&streamdata, rateIndex);
1022 if (err<0) // error check
1023 return err;
1024
1025 return 0;
1026}

1093/****************************************************************************
1094 * WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxPayloadSize(...)
1095 *
1096 * This function sets a limit for the maximum payload size of iSAC. The same
1097 * value is used both for 30 and 60 msec packets.
1098 * The absolute max will be valid until next time the function is called.
1099 * NOTE! This function may override the function WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxRate()
1100 *
1101 * Input:
1102 * - ISAC_main_inst : iSAC instance
1103 * - maxPayloadBytes : maximum size of the payload in bytes
1104 * valid values are between 100 and 400 bytes
1105 *
1106 *
1107 * Return value : 0 if sucessful
1108 * -1 if error happens
1109 */
1110
1111int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxPayloadSize(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
1112 int16_t maxPayloadBytes)
1113{
1114 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
1115
1116 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
1117 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
1118
1119 if((maxPayloadBytes < 100) || (maxPayloadBytes > 400))
1120 {
1121 /* maxPayloadBytes is out of valid range */
1122 return -1;
1123 }
1124 else
1125 {
1126 /* Set new absolute max, which will not change unless this function
1127 is called again with a new value */
1128 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes = maxPayloadBytes;
1129
1130 /* Set new maximum values for 30 and 60 msec packets */
1131 if (maxPayloadBytes < ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes) {
1132 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes30 = maxPayloadBytes;
1133 } else {
1134 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes30 = ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes;
1135 }
1136
1137 if ( maxPayloadBytes < (ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes << 1)) {
1138 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes60 = maxPayloadBytes;
1139 } else {
1140 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes60 = (ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes << 1);
1141 }
1142 }
1143 return 0;
1144}

1147/****************************************************************************
1148 * WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxRate(...)
1149 *
1150 * This function sets the maximum rate which the codec may not exceed for a
1151 * singel packet. The maximum rate is set in bits per second.
1152 * The codec has an absolute maximum rate of 53400 bits per second (200 bytes
1153 * per 30 msec).
1154 * It is possible to set a maximum rate between 32000 and 53400 bits per second.
1155 *
1156 * The rate limit is valid until next time the function is called.
1157 *
1158 * NOTE! Packet size will never go above the value set if calling
1159 * WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxPayloadSize() (default max packet size is 400 bytes).
1160 *
1161 * Input:
1162 * - ISAC_main_inst : iSAC instance
1163 * - maxRateInBytes : maximum rate in bits per second,
1164 * valid values are 32000 to 53400 bits
1165 *
1166 * Return value : 0 if sucessful
1167 * -1 if error happens
1168 */
1169
1170int16_t WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxRate(ISACFIX_MainStruct *ISAC_main_inst,
1171 int32_t maxRate)
1172{
1173 ISACFIX_SubStruct *ISAC_inst;
1174 int16_t maxRateInBytes;
1175
1176 /* typecast pointer to real structure */
1177 ISAC_inst = (ISACFIX_SubStruct *)ISAC_main_inst;
1178
1179 if((maxRate < 32000) || (maxRate > 53400))
1180 {
1181 /* maxRate is out of valid range */
1182 return -1;
1183 }
1184 else
1185 {
1186 /* Calculate maximum number of bytes per 30 msec packets for the given
1187 maximum rate. Multiply with 30/1000 to get number of bits per 30 msec,
1188 divide by 8 to get number of bytes per 30 msec:
1189 maxRateInBytes = floor((maxRate * 30/1000) / 8); */
1190 maxRateInBytes = (int16_t)( WebRtcSpl_DivW32W16ResW16(WEBRTC_SPL_MUL(maxRate, 3), 800) );
1191
1192 /* Store the value for usage in the WebRtcIsacfix_SetMaxPayloadSize-function */
1193 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxRateInBytes = maxRateInBytes;
1194
1195 /* For 30 msec packets: if the new limit is below the maximum
1196 payload size, set a new limit */
1197 if (maxRateInBytes < ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes) {
1198 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes30 = maxRateInBytes;
1199 } else {
1200 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes30 = ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes;
1201 }
1202
1203 /* For 60 msec packets: if the new limit (times 2) is below the
1204 maximum payload size, set a new limit */
1205 if ( (maxRateInBytes << 1) < ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes) {
1206 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes60 = (maxRateInBytes << 1);
1207 } else {
1208 ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.payloadLimitBytes60 = ISAC_inst->ISACenc_obj.maxPayloadBytes;
1209 }
1210 }
1211
1212 return 0;
1213}
